{
  "texts": [
    "These technologies are engineered to anonymise transactions, shield user identities, and prevent sensitive information from being divulged on the blockchain.",
    "Techniques such as zero-knowledge proofs and ring signatures enhance anonymity and confidentiality, allowing users to engage in transactions without revealing their identities (Mahmood and Vacius 2020).",
    "Additionally, cryptographic methods like homomorphic encryption safeguard sensitive data within the blockchain, ensuring that only authorised parties can access such information (Jin et al. 2019).",
    "Fig. 3 Data security issues of blockchain",
    "The seamless and secure sharing of information is one of the cornerstones of blockchain's appeal."
  ]
}